tip.text: Good value for money lunch & pretty delicious. $109 for the antipasti bar alone or get the salad bar free with any pasta or main.
Small intimate setting, good for dates. I loved the flower crab with uni. Sashimi selection is unique & the range of flavors is amazing. Good whisky dessert drinks (we tried cacao nibs and maple).
Amazing noodles - beef, ginger and spring onion, wonton - all good

tip.text: A true wellness retreat (no alcohol or smoking). Buffet brunch & dinner - vegetarian/vegan. Basic rooms are clean & bright. Beachfront yoga, cycling & core classes, paddle boards, steam room & pool.
Service is excellent. Rooms are quite run down BC the hotel is 7 years old, but the quality of resort is still high. Breakfast menu is healthy & tasty.

tip.text: The pho was excellent & pavlova meringue dessert was surprisingly delightful. Friendly staff.

tip.text: Bright space, good for solo dining. I wasn't that happy w/ my dish - had too much stuff on such a small plate that the food kept falling off. The coco loco drink was very good & staff was friendly.
Good value for money. Convenient location (have to cross major road traffic though). The rooms on the ground floor are noisy due to location. Staff is friendly and helpful.
Love the kareoke room. Cocktails are pretty good.
Salted fish is amazing and the squid ink rice is good too. For dessert - coconut pineapple shaved ice & ovaltine parfait are so good (that I actually had 2 desserts)
The view - grab a smoothie and sit on the plastic chairs to enjoy this view
Small rooms but great location
Cheap and convenient - no frills, not fancy and not quiet.
Good healthy cheap meals. Nice space to work in and good for casual meetings.
Excellent coworking space - downstairs canteen is good for meetings. Food is healthy & reasonably priced.
My favorite market! Loved the caneles, oysters, empanadas and chocolate covered strawberries. The perfect place to grab party desserts.
Good value lunch prefix £20. Quaint restaurant - quiet hotel in Bethnal green
Decent pastas at affordable prices. Excellent coffee. Friendly staff
Ginger onion noodles

formattedAddress: #05-03/#06-02, National Gallery Singapore (1 St Andrews Rd)

tip.text: Amazing scampi caviar pasta. The burrata and foie gras starters were good too, while the octopus starter was okay. Head up to the rooftop bar after dinner for a drink.

tip.text: Amazing. Cirque never disappoints.

venue.name: Cirque du Soleil - Totem Big Top in Singapore

tip.text: The cod roe creamy prawn pasta and black squid ink rice are amazing. Molten chocolate dessert too.
Overall good quality is excellent but service could be improved. My favorite dishes: king crab salad, octopus carpaccio, steak tenderloin, veal chop, lamb saddle & apricot lavender soufflé.
Young coconut is only 20,000 IDR. I like the gluten-free pasta, vegetarian melted cheese sandwich, Vietnamese salad rolls, and all their juices are good. Snacks to go- try the cheese kale 😍
Fantastic quaint hotel 5-10 min walk from Yoga Barn but away from the noise. $40/night including breakfast. Was in room Tekukur 1 which faces the rice fields- loved the view. Highly recommend!
The coconut curry laksa bowl was good. Service not great- servers are nice but slow, not vigilant and their English is so-so. Free wifi on 2nd floor. Password: livefood
They say that they sell at wholesale prices here. My Rudraksha necklace was 650,000 IDR less than in Singapore. Bought a sanskrit necklace "eternal love" that I really like.
Duck confit pasta was tasty, but pasta wasn't chewy. Shiraz wine okay. Come for ambience and if you are craving French food in Bali.

Trendy place with airy interiors & lots of light. The lunch is average but breakfast is better & cheaper. Efficient lunch spot for people in CBD. Staff is not always switched on & bathroom is outside.
We did a sake tasting which was educational. Food is excellent but pricey. All the dishes on the menu were excellent & creative, like using persimmon as a bowl. Ginkgo nut roasted w/ chestnuts good.
I love this bakery which is dog friendly! Tasty quiche & salted caramel tart. Blueberry muffin too. Adds to the atmosphere of Tiong Bahru.
Amazing luxury private island, perfect for a small group of friends. No air con. Staff was attentive & polite but not intrusive- Amazing service. Island has paddle boards & kayaks for you to use.

formattedAddress: Marina Bay Sands Singapore (10 Bayfront Avenue)

tip.text: Love their Caneles (often out of stock so get there early) and Macaroons.
Creative desserts on Keong Saik Road. Chill cafe, good for casual meetings & dates. Chocolate pudding with strawberries. You can take the flower pot home with you!
Excellent waffle pancakes (gluten-free option) and mushroom bruschetta. Good dumpling soup and vermicelli w/ garlic & chilli. Best organic cafe in Singapore with chill surroundings, but no service.
Not as good as the original Canadian chain but it will give you a sweet taste of home (if you're Canadian). Cheeseburger with Triple-O sauce is classic.

formattedAddress: #02-14 Asia Square Tower 1 Food Garden (8 Marina View)

tip.text: Excellent Udon dishes, good for quick lunch. The duck black pepper udon, mentaiko beef udon and classic zaru udon are good.
Wasn't expecting much from a cafe at ION but was pleasantly surprised. I liked the steak with mash - get it medium rare. Egg Confit is a good appetizer.
Favorite yakitori place in SG- quality & freshness of food is excellent. LOVE the Gingko nuts. Other favorites: garlic fried rice, foie gras, mochi w/ pork, Kazu pancake balls, wagyu beef w/ enoki.

formattedAddress: 1380 Ang Mo Kio Ave 1 (Bishan - Ang Mo Kio Park)

tip.text: Excellent italian food and service. Get a table in the back - not the bar area. The Sardinian lobster fregola is good value for money. Chocolate profiteroles dessert was really good too.

Really good oysters, lamb and bone marrow. The chocolate gift box they give you after dinner is a nice touch. Great service and excellent music playlist (90s-early 2000s). Highly recommend this resto!
The mussels and clams appetizer was good. Conveniently located near bars- jigger & pony & sugarhall that you can hop over to after.
Very nice pool for low key weekend parties. Bathroom & bar logistics could be improved though
Grooming, daycare, healthy dog food & treats
Highly recommend their grooming & daycare. Great service, good location. My dog goes 4 days/week and he's always happy!
Really good, highly recommend for dates and groups. Favorite dish was salmon roe omelette. Also good: crab & avocado salad, white asparagus & lambchops

Clean minimalist 80s looking hotel with tones of summer beach cottage decor. Friendly staff & surprisingly good room service food. Get a seaview room & watch the sunset from your balcony.
Fantastic bite sized tapas. You just take from a selection at the bar and they tally up your sticks after.
